						<summary>

						<p>West wall of the central shrine in the Bṛihadīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kulōttuṅga I year 41: 1110-11 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged and incomplete inscription contains parts of the kingds <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> beginning with <hi rend="italic">Pugaḻ-śūḻnda-puṇari,</hi> etc.</p>						

						<p>The first of the three verses in Sanskrit language and written in Grantha characters invoke the goddess Śrī (i.e., Lakshmī), while the other two verses trace the genealogy of the Gāhaḍavāla kings of Kanauj viz., Yaśōvigraha, Mahīchandra and śrī Chandradēva.</p>						

						</summary>
